Comparing Tranquility (Build: 2684044) to Singularity (Build: 2667341)

Want to be notified of new patches? Hop into #hoboleaks on Tweetfleet Slack! Instructions on how to join Tweetfleet Slack here.
Please note that Singularity will be kept inaccessible except for specific testing windows, and may fall significantly behind Tranquility in patches. The Tranquility/Singularity diff (homepage) may not be particularly useful for the time being. Refer to the latest Tranquility patches instead.

New! Find Hoboleaks useful and want to provide some support, at no additional cost to yourself?
Use affiliate code HL (short for HoboLeaks) the next time you make a purchase through the official EVE store, which has Omega, PLEX, and much more. Thank you for helping Hoboleaks remain ad-free! ♥

84398 - Decayed Large EMP Smartbomb Mutaplasmid This bioadaptive mutaplasmid tool is designed to interface with and alter devices that can radiate omnidirectional pulses. As such this mutaplasmid could be used to mutate the performance characteristics of smartbomb modules.

Triglavian bioadaptive technology makes extensive use of engineered colonies of extremophilic bacteria, that are used to grow, harvest and adapt various resources found in Abyssal Deadspace. Artificial colonizing plasmids integrated into specialist tools used for direct adaptation of technology can be found in Triglavian caches in various stages of development. These mutaplasmids can be used to alter the characteristics of a wide variety of equipment types, depending on the strain and the bioadaptive tool with which they are integrated.

The mutaplasmid colony integrated into this bioadaptive tool has begun to decay and mutation effects will be less pronounced as a result. While possible mutational benefits are low, the risks of using this mutaplasmid are also reduced.		 Mutaplasmids

710826 The Upwell Consortium, renowned for its successful Athanor and Tatara class refineries, recognized the mounting challenges faced by its customers with moon-mining operations. In response, they unveiled the Metenox moon drill, a hands-off deployable employing traditional surface-grazing techniques.

Although these autonomous facilities are less efficient at material extraction than refineries and are more vulnerable to raids due to lighter plating, short reinforcement windows, and also garner high power demands requiring colony reagents, the Consortium insists that their autonomous functionality is a worthy trade-off.

Please note: The Metenox moon drill must be positioned within 250km of an eligible moon mining site and exclusively in systems rated 0.4 security or lower. In response, they unveiled the Metenox moon drill, a hands-off deployable employing traditional surface-grazing techniques.

While these autonomous facilities extract materials less efficiently than refineries, they offer scalability by mining multiple moons with individual Metenox at once.
